description:
Hi there!
I'm Kristin and I love my apartment. I've been an Airbnb-er for years now but just now becoming a host (Aug 2016).

My place is very close to Prospect Park - the better end in my opinion! Lots of activities going on, the lake, roller rink, markets, the boathouse. Erv's, Blessings, Nagle's Bagels. 

Much more space than your average NYC apt. In a diverse neighborhood, plenty of character, the PARK & great train access.

Good for couples, solo adventurers, & business travelers.

Tons of books - especially on art.
A bike!
Sunlight/windows
Elevator
Breakfast/coffee
Kitchen tools

The whole place! Please respect furniture, kitchen items, etc. Welcome to use the hall closet across from the kitchen if needed.

It's likely I'll be in town or nearby during your stay. If not, there will be someone to meet you, give keys and help out.

Prospect Lefferts Gardens is a newly gentrified area - originally (and still) very Caribbean. Which means, great food. You'll smell it in the building even ;)

Coffee shops, bars, etc are popping up everywhere. Nearby is Crown Heights which has just went through this process and is very popular.

The Q train is express and the best train for this apartment - it runs all through Manhattan and connects to lots of trains (download the iTrans app if you don't have it). The B is also at this stop and runs during rush hour.

You can also use the S (shuttle train) to connect to the C, 2, 3, 4, 5 just one to three stops away. The S will also take you right to the Botanical Gardens, the Zoo and near the Brooklyn Museum (off the 2, 3).

The Barclays Center is also not far at all.

Be sure to check MTA signage in the stations - especially for late nights and weekends!

New Yorkers love giving directions, so if you're stressed or lost, just ask someone. They're proud to have learned our extensive transit lines ;)

A 20minute walk across the park (use Centre street/path) and you can catch the F, G trains at the 15th St stop. Otherwise, the Q doesn't really connect to these two trains.

Lyft is all over and often have promos. Uber too, but I don't prefer them.  Gett is a new company, also Car2Go is available if you have a membership.

hosts.about:
Hello!
I have been using airbnb for some years now and it's my favorite way to book lodging while traveling.  Typically, I'm out all day and night exploring the city/town I've traveled to.  Unfortunately, all I do in the bnb's are sleep and shower haha.  I still love being in someone's home and feeling more welcome/comfortable than a hostel or hotel.  Currently, I live in Brooklyn, NY and can always give my hosts tips on traveling there if desired.
Hope to meet you soon!

Location was perfect, subway nearby, lovely cafe's, shops and Caribbean Vibes. Great mix of cultures! Thank you Kristin 
ps Say Hello when you ever come to Holland;)
